__NOTOC__

== Measures of Central Tendency ==
Numerical values that find the center of a set of data are known as the '''measures of central tendency'''.  All measures of central tendency are associated with the term ''average''.

{{BookCat}}

== ''z'' test statistic: one proportion ==
A test statistic that represents the difference between the hypothesized proportion and the observed proportion is used when the binomial parameter ''p'' is being tested through the use of a hypothesis-testing procedure.  This value is then divided by the standard error.  When ''n'' is significantly large (''n'' > 20, ''np'' > 5, and ''nq'' > 5), the test assumptions have been satisfied, and the null hypothesis is true, then we assume that the test statistic is normally distributed.

{{AltBookCat}}

== ''z'' test statistic: two proportions ==
The '''test statistic''' is the difference between the observed proportions divided by the '''standard error''' when the hypothesis being tested is '''there is no difference between the two proportions'''.

{{AltBookCat}}

