==Synopsis== \afterassignment<command>...<command>
== Description== All commands that follow as a parameter are stored and their interpretation is delayed until the next assignment. This can be used for making loops.
{{BookCat}}

== Synopsis== \begingroup
==Description== Starts a new group, exactly like {. See also [[TeX/endgroup|\endgroup]].
{{BookCat}}

==Synopsis== \endgroup
==Description== End the current group. See also [[TeX/begingroup|\begingroup]].
{{BookCat}}

==Synopsis== \box<0..255>
==Description== <tt>\boxN</tt> outputs the content of box register <tt>N</tt>, with <tt>N</tt> between 0 and 255. Box registers can be set using [[TeX/setbox|\setboxN]].
{{BookCat}}

==Synopsis== \boxmaxdepth
==Description== Maximum depth of a box. The default is <tt>\maxdimen</tt>.
{{BookCat}}

==Synopsis== \cleaders<object><skip>
==Description== The contents of <tt><nowiki><object></nowiki></tt> (<tt>\hbox</tt>, <tt>\vbox</tt>, <tt>\vrule</tt> or <tt>\hrule</tt>) will be repeated as often as the following <tt><nowiki><skip></nowiki></tt> determines.
{{BookCat}}

==Synopsis== \closein <file id>
==Description== Closes an additional input file, described by its number from 0 to 15. See also [[TeX/openin|\openin]], [[TeX/read|\read]] and [[TeX/newread|\newread]].
{{BookCat}}

==Synopsis== \closeout <file id>
==Description== Closes an additional output file, described by its file id, which is a number between 0 and 15. See also [[TeX/openout|\openout]], [[TeX/write|\write]] and [[TeX/newwrite|\newwrite]].
{{BookCat}}

==Synopsis== \copy<number>
==Description== <tt>\copyN</tt> copies the content of box register <tt>N</tt>. The old contents remain.
{{BookCat}}

==Synopsis== \countdef\<name>=<0..255>
==Description== Defines a symbolic name for a count register (0..255). For instance, plain TeX defines <tt>\countdef\pageno=0</tt>.
{{BookCat}}

==Synopsis== \crcr
==Description== Generates a <tt>\cr</tt> if no <tt>\cr</tt> is following. Usualy used in macros.
{{BookCat}}

==Synopsis==
 \csname
==Description==
Used with <tt>\endcsname</tt>. The text between the two commands build the name of a TeX command.

==Example==
<source lang="latex">
 \def\x{paragraph}

 % \def\startparagraph#1{...}
 \def\csname start\x\endcsname#1{...}

 % \def\stopparagraph#1{...}
 \def\csname stop\x\endcsname#1{...} 

 % \startparagraph{mytext}
 \csname start\x\endcsname{mytext}
</source>
{{BookCat}}

==Synopsis== \defaulthyphenchar=<char code>
==Description== Initializes the default hypenation character, defined with [[TeX/hyphenchar|<tt>\hyphenchar</tt>]] at the beginning of a [[TeX/font|<tt>\font</tt>]] command.
{{BookCat}}

.pBody {background-color: #666666; color: #eeeeee}
.pBody a:link {color: #99ffcc}
.pBody a:visited {color: #ffcc99}
.pBody a:hover {color: #99ccff}
#searchInput {background-color: #cccccc; color: #000000; font-family: monospace}

