Like Maxwell's equations describe light wave equations in the same way Schrodinger's equations describe equations of matter waves.

The equation was discovered by an Austrian physicist, Erwin Schrodinger in 1926.  Schrodinger's equations involve complex mathematics and up to now several solutions to the  equations have been derived for different situations. 

