owers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Phytolacca americana|White Flowers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Plantago lanceolata|White Flowers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Dalibarda repens|White Flowers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Mitchella repens|White Flowers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Gaultheria procumbens|White Flowers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Chimaphila umbellata|White Flowers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Monotropa uniflora|White Flowers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Sagittaria|White Flowers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Cicuta maculata|White Flowers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Nymphaea odorata|White Flowers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Nymphoides cordata|White Flowers]] ;Summer Flowers of Northern New England :[[Wikijunior:Summer Flowers of Northern New England/Eriocaulon aquaticum|White Flowers]]
[[Category:Collections|Summer Flowers of Northern New England]]

Often, the difference between success and failure as a young adult writer comes down to your ability to truly ''read'' young adult literature, and understand the mechanics behind it. The most important skill you will ever learn is how to read like a writer: how to distinguish good fiction from bad, an enthralling read from a dull one. Through reading the instant classics of the new generation: J.K. Rowling's ''Harry Potter,'' Ann Brashares's ''The Sisterhood of the Traveling Pants,'' and Suzanne Collins's ''The Hunger Games'' to name a few, you will hopefully gain greater insight into what will make your book a success and what will mark it for failure from day one. 

The "chapters" are in no particular order, the book titles are organized by genre. This book is essentially an extended reading guide from a young adult writer's perspective.

